net.ashwork.functionality.operator

Interface OperatorN<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the operands and result of the operator
    All Superinterfaces:
    net.ashwork.functionality.partial.Arity, net.ashwork.functionality.FunctionN<T>, net.ashwork.functionality.partial.ResultChainable<T>, net.ashwork.functionality.partial.ResultChainableResult<T>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    BooleanOperator1, BooleanOperator2, ByteOperator1, ByteOperator2, CharOperator1, CharOperator2, DoubleOperator1, DoubleOperator2, FloatOperator1, FloatOperator2, IntOperator1, IntOperator2, LongOperator1, LongOperator2, Operator1<T>, Operator2<T>, ShortOperator1, ShortOperator2
    All Known Implementing Classes:

    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface OperatorN<T>
extends net.ashwork.functionality.FunctionN<T>
    Represents an operation that accepts n operands and produces a result of the same type as its operands. All operators are derived from this n-arity specialization. This is a specialization of FunctionN where the operands and result are of the same type.

    This is a functional interface whose functional method is FunctionN.applyAllUnchecked(Object...).

    Since:
    1.0.0
